: 1070.64, "text": " Out."}, {"start": 1070.64, "end": 1071.64, "text": " What."}, {"start": 1071.64, "end": 1072.64, "text": " Is."}, {"start": 1072.64, "end": 1073.64, "text": " The."}, {"start": 1073.64, "end": 1074.64, "text": " Cause."}, {"start": 1074.64, "end": 1075.64, "text": " In."}, {"start": 1075.64, "end": 1076.64, "text": " Theory."}, {"start": 1076.64, "end": 1077.64, "text": " Not."}, {"start": 1077.64, "end": 1078.64, "text": " Duality."}, {"start": 1078.64, "end": 1079.64, "text": " That."}, {"start": 1079.64, "end": 1080.64, "text": " Means."}, {"start": 1080.64, "end": 1081.64, "text": " The."}, {"start": 1081.64, "end": 1082.64, "text": " Come."}, {"start": 1082.64, "end": 1083.64, "text": " Up."}, {"start": 1083.64, "end": 1084.64, "text": " To."}, {"start": 1084.64, "end": 1085.64, "text": " Impersonalism."}, {"start": 1085.64, "end": 1086.64, "text": " To."}, {"start": 1086.64, "end": 1087.64, "text": " Figure."}, {"start": 1087.64, "end": 1088.64, "text": " Out."}, {"start": 1088.64, "end": 1089.64, "text": " Whether."}, {"start": 1089.64, "end": 1090.64, "text": " This."}, {"start": 1090.64, "end": 1091.64, "text": " Is."}, {"start": 1091.64, "end": 1092.64, "text": " The."}, {"start": 1092.64, "end": 1093.64, "text": " Cause."}, {"start": 1093.64, "end": 1094.64, "text": " But."}, {"start": 1094.64, "end": 1095.64, "text": " Here."}, {"start": 1095.64, "end": 1096.64, "text": " It."}, {"start": 1096.64, "end": 1097.64, "text": " Is."}, {"start": 1097.64, "end": 1098.64, "text": " Mentioned."}, {"start": 1098.64, "end": 1099.64, "text": " Here."}, {"start": 1099.64, "end": 1100.64, "text": " Yes."}, {"start": 1100.64, "end": 1101.64, "text": " Men."}, {"start": 1101.64, "end": 1102.64, "text": " Who."}, {"start": 1102.64, "end": 1103.64, "text": " Gain."}, {"start": 1103.64, "end": 1104.64, "text": " Chin."}, {"start": 1104.64, "end": 1107.64, "text": " The supreme Brahman is the Hetu."}, {"start": 1109.64, "end": 1111.64, "text": " Brahman means the greatest."}, {"start": 1113.64, "end": 1117.64, "text": " Supreme Brahman means the supremely greatest, supreme personality of Godhead."}, {"start": 1118.64, "end": 1122.64, "text": " What is greatest? Again there is a lot of discussion."}, {"start": 1124.64, "end": 1133.64, "text": " So people ultimately because they exercise their intelligence to figure out, they can maximum come to this impersonal Brahmajyothi."}, {"start": 1134.64, "end": 1136.64, "text": " They think that is the greatest."}, {"start": 1138.64, "end": 1147.64, "text": " So devotees who come in touch with Srila Prabhupada and Krishna consciousness, they know that impersonal Brahman is not the greatest."}, {"start": 1148.64, "end": 1155.64, "text": " It is greatest but it is also having a source and that source is the supreme personality of Godhead himself."}, {"start": 1156.64, "end": 1160.64, "text": " So that's why here Tad-Brahma indicates the supreme Brahman."}, {"start": 1161.64, "end": 1163.64, "text": " Tad-Detu means supreme."}, {"start": 1164.64, "end": 1165.64, "text": " Krishna is the Hetu."}, {"start": 1166.64, "end": 1168.64, "text": " Krishna is the Hetu."}, {"start": 1169.64, "end": 1171.64, "text": " Krishna is the cause of all causes."}, {"start": 1172.64, "end": 1178.64, "text": " This is what? The conclusion of Bhagavad Gita, Bhagavatam and Brahma Samhita."}, {"start": 1179.64, "end": 1191.64, "text": " Anything less than this, if somebody analyzing the cause for some issue and if they fall short of reaching this conclusion"}, {"start": 1191.64, "end": 1199.64, "text": " that Krishna is the cause of all causes, then his calculation is not complete."}, {"start": 1200.64, "end": 1206.64, "text": " Like for example they have mentioned all these causes and they have mentioned the solutions."}, {"start": 1207.64, "end": 1214.64, "text": " So if the Krishna is not there in the equation and when they come up with the solutions, then what happens?"}, {"start": 1215.64, "end": 1220.64, "text": " That Prahalad Maharaj explains that such solutions will be much more problematic."}, {"start": 1220.64, "end": 1225.64, "text": " Much more problematic than the original problems."}, {"start": 1226.64, "end": 1233.64, "text": " For example there are solutions about how you should cross over suicidal tendencies."}, {"start": 1234.64, "end": 1236.64, "text": " Big, big books are there."}, {"start": 1237.64, "end": 1240.64, "text": " And then how to come out of addictions and habits."}, {"start": 1241.64, "end": 1243.64, "text": " Big, big books are there."}, {"start": 1243.64, "end": 1249.64, "text": " In some of the countries they have a de-addiction center for Facebook alone."}, {"start": 1250.64, "end": 1253.64, "text": " Facebook building, then there is a Google building."}, {"start": 1258.64, "end": 1260.64, "text": " Continuously searching."}, {"start": 1261.64, "end": 1265.64, "text": " And then after he comes out of the gadget also the hands are not stopping."}, {"start": 1268.64, "end": 1271.64, "text": " So that has become a disease."}, {"start": 1271.64, "end": 1273.64, "text": " So they have like that."}, {"start": 1274.64, "end": 1279.64, "text": " Somebody may say, no I don't have Facebook depression nowadays because I am using Instagram."}, {"start": 1280.64, "end": 1282.64, "text": " That is becoming very popular."}, {"start": 1283.64, "end": 1286.64, "text": " Don't worry, very soon Instagram building also will come up."}, {"start": 1287.64, "end": 1292.64, "text": " So for each of these symptoms, they are coming up with solution."}, {"start": 1293.64, "end": 1295.64, "text": " But those solutions are much bigger problems."}, {"start": 1295.64, "end": 1308.64, "text": " So that is why here it is clearly mentioned, sarvakarana karanam."}, {"start": 1309.64, "end": 1312.64, "text": " Krishna is also known as karanatmane."}, {"start": 1313.64, "end": 1318.64, "text": " His very body, his transcendental body is the cause."}, {"start": 1319.64, "end": 1322.64, "text": " As soon as we don't see Krishna's body,"}, {"start": 1322.64, "end": 1326.64, "text": " then our thinking gets into duality."}, {"start": 1327.64, "end": 1332.64, "text": " We get attracted by some things and we get repelled by some things."}, {"start": 1333.64, "end": 1340.64, "text": " The first symptom of not seeing Krishna's transcendental form is that we get into duality."}, {"start": 1341.64, "end": 1348.64, "text": " Our mind starts thinking in terms of plus and minus or something is attractive and something is not."}, {"start": 1349.64, "end": 1351.64, "text": " Consciousness gets repelled by some things."}, {"start": 1352.64, "end": 1354.64, "text": " And consciousness gets attracted by some things."}, {"start": 1355.64, "end": 1356.64, "text": " This is the phenomenon."}, {"start": 1357.64, "end": 1360.64, "text": " That is why some people get attracted to this channel, some people to that channel."}, {"start": 1361.64, "end": 1363.64, "text": " Somebody may not have that much of an attraction."}, {"start": 1364.64, "end": 1370.64, "text": " Everything can be explained if you understand that if Krishna is not there in the picture,"}, {"start": 1371.64, "end": 1372.64, "text": " then comes the duality."}, {"start": 1373.64, "end": 1376.64, "text": " That is why some people are able to figure out duality is an issue."}, {"start": 1377.64, "end": 1381.64, "text": " But their analysis, their final conclusion is not correct."}, {"start": 1382.64, "end": 1383.64, "text": " It is incomplete."}, {"start": 1384.64, "end": 1390.64, "text": " Because they have not yet understood the tad brahma tad hetu ho."}, {"start": 1391.64, "end": 1399.64, "text": " So whenever we are caught up in these dualities,"}, {"start": 1400.64, "end": 1405.64, "text": " getting attracted to something and getting repelled by something,"}, {"start": 1406.64, "end": 1410.64, "text": " we should know that Krishna is missing in the equation."}, {"start": 1410.64, "end": 1413.64, "text": " And that is why we are struggling in our minds."}, {"start": 1414.64, "end": 1421.64, "text": " So this attraction and repulsion, they are not static like that."}, {"start": 1422.64, "end": 1424.64, "text": " We move between these two."}, {"start": 1425.64, "end": 1432.64, "text": " You know, sometimes you may be attracted towards one particular object, a particular person."}, {"start": 1433.64, "end": 1437.64, "text": " And then slowly, by your calculation,"}, {"start": 1437.64, "end": 1441.64, "text": " you may detach yourself and then go to the other extreme of repulsion."}, {"start": 1442.64, "end": 1443.64, "text": " No, no, I hate this."}, {"start": 1444.64, "end": 1445.64, "text": " You may say."}, {"start": 1446.64, "end": 1447.64, "text": " And then hating, hating, hating."}, {"start": 1448.64, "end": 1452.64, "text": " After some time, you will see again it will move back towards the attraction."}, {"start": 1453.64, "end": 1457.64, "text": " This pendulum, the duality of pendulum, this is called habit."}, {"start": 1458.64, "end": 1460.64, "text": " Habits are like this, pendulums."}, {"start": 1461.64, "end": 1466.64, "text": " We will be forced to do something and then we become detached from it and we move away from it."}, {"start": 1466.64, "end": 1468.64, "text": " And again we will be forced in it."}, {"start": 1469.64, "end": 1478.64, "text": " So pendulums indicate that Krishna, somehow we are not able to see Krishna as a cause there."}, {"start": 1479.64, "end": 1481.64, "text": " In the Chathashloki Bhagavatam also Krishna explains,"}, {"start": 1482.64, "end": 1489.64, "text": " if anybody sees something existing without my connection, that is Maya."}, {"start": 1490.64, "end": 1495.64, "text": " So that means Maya's first symptom is we will be caught up in this duality."}, {"start": 1497.64, "end": 1505.64, "text": " So that's why when we are caught up like that, it is difficult for us to cross over on our own."}, {"start": 1506.64, "end": 1511.64, "text": " We have to take shelter of the spiritual master, take shelter of other Vaishnavas."}, {"start": 1512.64, "end": 1518.64, "text": " Go and explain about the pendulums in our consciousness."}, {"start": 1519.64, "end": 1524.64, "text": " Take their help so that we become fixed in one."}, {"start": 1524.64, "end": 1530.64, "text": " Ananyad ekam, everything is one without any second and that is Krishna."}, {"start": 1531.64, "end": 1540.64, "text": " So if we can figure out Krishna in every situation, if we can see connection with Krishna in every situation,"}, {"start": 1541.64, "end": 1546.64, "text": " then only we can be free from these anxieties of dualities."}, {"start": 1547.64, "end": 1550.64, "text": " Otherwise we will be caught up."}, {"start": 1550.64, "end": 1555.64, "text": " So that's why Prabhupada is mentioning in the purport, he is quoting from Madhavacharya,"}, {"start": 1556.64, "end": 1562.64, "text": " that ultimately the Krishna's blissful transcendental body is a cause of all causes."}, {"start": 1563.64, "end": 1568.64, "text": " Here there is one more word is there, yasmai."}, {"start": 1569.64, "end": 1575.64, "text": " Yasmai means actually everything is coming from him, everything belongs to him."}, {"start": 1576.64, "end": 1579.64, "text": " And then everything has to be offered to him."}, {"start": 1580.64, "end": 1583.64, "text": " Actually these statements look very simple."}, {"start": 1584.64, "end": 1592.64, "text": " But if we have no realization of that, again we will be put into this duality."}, {"start": 1593.64, "end": 1596.64, "text": " Again we get attracted, again we become repulsed."}, {"start": 1597.64, "end": 1602.64, "text": " So that's why each of these qualities are attributes of the Supreme Lord Krishna."}, {"start": 1603.64, "end": 1609.64, "text": " We have to meditate, we have to ensure, we have to meditate and then it has to sink in."}, {"start": 1610.64, "end": 1616.64, "text": " Again yasmai means offering, everything has to be offered to him."}, {"start": 1617.64, "end": 1626.64, "text": " As devotees, practicing devotees, we are offering many things every day."}, {"start": 1627.64, "end": 1634.64, "text": " Our devotional service is very important aspect of our lives."}, {"start": 1635.64, "end": 1639.64, "text": " That is the ultimate conclusion of everything of Krishna conscious life is,"}, {"start": 1640.64, "end": 1642.64, "text": " our offerings."}, {"start": 1643.64, "end": 1650.64, "text": " Our offerings to our spiritual master, our offerings to the Supreme Personality of Godhead."}, {"start": 1651.64, "end": 1657.64, "text": " So when we are about to offer something, we should ensure that we have,"}, {"start": 1658.64, "end": 1664.64, "text": " we don't mix up our ignorance into our offering."}, {"start": 1665.64, "end": 1667.64, "text": " We don't mix up our ignorance."}, {"start": 1667.64, "end": 1671.64, "text": " There are six things that Krishna explains in Bhagavad Gita."}, {"start": 1672.64, "end": 1677.64, "text": " We should ensure that our offering doesn't have these six items."}, {"start": 1678.64, "end": 1680.64, "text": " One is anubhandam."}, {"start": 1681.64, "end": 1687.64, "text": " Anubhandam means without future bondage."}, {"start": 1688.64, "end": 1695.64, "text": " Before we begin anything, little bit of calculation should be there whether it will bind me."}, {"start": 1695.64, "end": 1700.64, "text": " Consequences, whether it will bind me, one has to calculate."}, {"start": 1701.64, "end": 1705.64, "text": " Then shayam, shayam means distraction."}, {"start": 1706.64, "end": 1713.64, "text": " That means instead of focusing on the service at hand, am I getting distracted, distracting myself."}, {"start": 1714.64, "end": 1718.64, "text": " Sometimes if the service is little big, mind will not go towards it."}, {"start": 1719.64, "end": 1720.64, "text": " That's the tendency of the mind."}, {"start": 1720.64, "end": 1724.64, "text": " Anything big or anything unknown, tries to postpone."}, {"start": 1725.64, "end": 1733.64, "text": " Keep the work aside and distract ourselves with browsing something, clicking something and putting something."}, {"start": 1734.64, "end": 1735.64, "text": " This is takshayam."}, {"start": 1736.64, "end": 1741.64, "text": " And then himsam, himsam means any violence."}, {"start": 1742.64, "end": 1749.64, "text": " This action, this offering, a so-called offering, is it going to be creating?"}, {"start": 1750.64, "end": 1752.64, "text": " Any himsam, violence."}, {"start": 1753.64, "end": 1754.64, "text": " And then anapeksha."}, {"start": 1755.64, "end": 1768.64, "text": " Anapeksha means consideration without considering the scriptural directions."}, {"start": 1769.64, "end": 1771.64, "text": " Anapeksha, udhasina, anapeksha."}, {"start": 1772.64, "end": 1777.64, "text": " We don't consider the regulations, the rules and regulations."}, {"start": 1778.64, "end": 1779.64, "text": " And then paurusham."}, {"start": 1780.64, "end": 1785.64, "text": " That means it is self-assigned."}, {"start": 1786.64, "end": 1790.64, "text": " We assume, okay, this is okay, paurusham."}, {"start": 1791.64, "end": 1794.64, "text": " And then mohat, out of illusion."}, {"start": 1795.64, "end": 1797.64, "text": " Illusion means impractical."}, {"start": 1798.64, "end": 1802.64, "text": " Sometimes we may start something which could be impractical."}, {"start": 1803.64, "end": 1807.64, "text": " So yes, offerings are there, we are offering every day."}, {"start": 1807.64, "end": 1816.64, "text": " And we wanted to, but we have to offer, ensuring that these six ignorant things don't get mixed up."}, {"start": 1817.64, "end": 1821.64, "text": " So then our devotional service will become pure day by day."}, {"start": 1822.64, "end": 1830.64, "text": " So how to bring in Krishna into our life more and more, into some situation, into our problems?"}, {"start": 1830.64, "end": 1837.64, "text": " That is made very easy by Prabhupada through this chanting."}, {"start": 1838.64, "end": 1845.64, "text": " Hare Krishna, Hare Krishna, Krishna Krishna, Hare Hare, Hare Rama, Hare Rama, Rama Rama,"}, {"start": 1846.64, "end": 1850.64, "text": " Sri Prabhupada ki jaya, Srimad Bhagavatam ki jaya."}]}